ObservaTrans

AI Platform for Monitoring Anti-LGBTQIA+ Violence and Disinformation

Overview

ObservaTrans is a civic technology platform designed to monitor anti-LGBTQIA+ disinformation, document institutional violence, and generate structured data about violence affecting trans and travesti communities in Brazil.

Brazil has remained the country with the highest number of murders of trans people in the world for more than 17 consecutive years. Despite the severity of this situation, there is still no integrated public infrastructure capable of documenting institutional discrimination, tracking misinformation targeting LGBTQIA+ communities, and systematizing reliable data on violence affecting trans populations.

This project aims to address this gap by developing a digital platform that combines community reporting tools, artificial intelligence, and open data infrastructure.

Key Features

The platform will include four main components:

1. Institutional Violence Reporting System

A secure digital interface where LGBTQIA+ individuals can report discrimination and violence experienced in public services such as healthcare, education, policing, and social assistance.

2. AI-Based Misinformation Monitoring

Natural language processing tools will analyze publicly available online content to detect anti-LGBTQIA+ misinformation, hate speech, and coordinated disinformation narratives.

3. Data Infrastructure on Anti-Trans Violence

The platform will build a structured database documenting cases of lethal violence against trans and travesti individuals using verified media sources and civil society reports.

4. Civil Society Case Support Network

LGBTQIA+ organizations will be able to register and support reported cases by providing legal, social, or psychological assistance.

Technology Stack

Planned technologies include:

Python

Natural Language Processing (spaCy / Transformers)

PostgreSQL + PostGIS

Cloud infrastructure

Data visualization dashboards

Secure reporting architecture

The project prioritizes open-source technologies and transparent methodologies.

Democratic Impact

ObservaTrans strengthens democratic accountability by making violence and disinformation affecting LGBTQIA+ communities visible through structured data.

The platform supports:

transparency about institutional discrimination

monitoring of harmful online narratives

evidence-based advocacy

public datasets for research and journalism

By transforming dispersed information into structured and accessible data, the platform contributes to protecting civic space and promoting human rights.

Community and Partnerships

The project is led by Rede Inclusivah!, a Brazilian civil society organization focused on LGBTQIA+ health and human rights.

Technical development is supported through collaboration with:

Instituto Metrópole Digital – Federal University of Rio Grande do Norte (UFRN)

Federal Institute of Rio Grande do Norte (IFRN)

Pajubá Tech (startup partner)

The development team includes a trans man software developer and a trans woman systems analyst, ensuring direct participation from the communities most affected by the issues the platform addresses.

Project Status

Early prototype stage.

The current phase focuses on:

architecture design

data model development

prototype interfaces

validation with civil society organizations.

Vision

The long-term goal is to establish ObservaTrans as a public data infrastructure supporting journalists, researchers, human rights organizations, and policymakers working to combat violence and disinformation affecting LGBTQIA+ communities.
